questiontext.text: A random sample of 50 cars in the drive-thru of a popular fast food restaurant revealed an average bill of $18.21 per car. The population standard deviation is $5.92. Find the lower limit of a 98% confidence interval for the mean bill for all cars in the drive-thru. Round your answer to the nearest cent; do not include the dollar sign in your answer.
